               <p>1254. <persName id="def1-1254-18500708" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1254-18500708" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1254-18500708" type="age" value="24"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1254-18500708" type="surname" value="WERNDLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1254-18500708" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM WERNDLEY</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18500708-1254-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18500708-1254-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18500708-1254-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp>, unlawfully uttering counterfeit coin.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MESSRS. ELLIS</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">BODKIN</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18500708-name-168" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-168" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-168" type="surname" value="PREW"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-168" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN PREW</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Oxford-street, and am a hosier. On 27th June, about ten o'clock at night, I saw some men standing near my shop; the prisoner was one of them—I asked if he wanted to buy a pair of braces—he came into the shop—the price of them was 10<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he gave me a bad shilling—I said, "You rascal, you knew it was bad," and ordered him out of the shop—he said he was sure it was good—he went away, and was brought back by a policeman in a few minutes—I saw a bad shilling found on him—I gave the policeman the shilling the prisoner gave me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18500708-name-169" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-169" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-169" type="surname" value="M'LASKEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-169" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES M'LASKEY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, C</hi> 101). I took the prisoner about ten o'clock, after running about 200 yards, and asked him what he was running for—he said, "For a lark"—I took him back to Mr. Prew, and found on him 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 8<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. in good silver, and this bad shilling(<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>)in a purse with the good silver; also 9 1/2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. in copper—I received this other shilling from Mr. Prew.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18500708-name-170" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-170" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-170" type="surname" value="WEBSTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500708-name-170" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM WEBSTER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am inspector of coin to the Royal Mint. These two shillings are both counterfeit, and from the same mould.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I had changed half-a-crown, and taken the two shillings; I took one to the shop, the other was in my bag.</p>
               <p>
